{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_31","type":"agent_message","text":"I have the shape now. I’m going with `@tanstack/react-query` for backend-owned session data and a tiny per-session external store for runtime-only state, instead of bringing in a second dependency for local state. That keeps the responsibilities explicit: query cache for snapshots, local store for pending actions and live feed bookkeeping."}}
