{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_109","type":"agent_message","text":"Implemented the frontend state foundation and committed the code changes as `4f60ccf` (`feat(prompt-23): frontend state foundation`). The main pieces are the shared React Query layer in [AppProviders.tsx](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/app/AppProviders.tsx) and [queryClient.ts](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/app/queryClient.ts), the new session hooks in [sessionQueries.ts](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/features/session/sessionQueries.ts), and the per-session runtime store/context in [sessionRuntimeStore.ts](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/features/session/sessionRuntimeStore.ts) and [sessionWorkspaceContext.ts](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/features/session/sessionWorkspaceContext.ts). [HomePage.tsx](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx) and [SessionWorkspacePage.tsx](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx) now consume that state layer, and the short architecture note is in [frontend-state-architecture.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/frontend-state-architecture.md).\n\nVerification passed with `npm test`, `npm run lint`, and `npm run build` in `frontend/`, plus browser checks and screenshots for the home and workspace routes. The required reviewer summary was written last to [23-frontend-state-foundation.summary.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/prompts/23-frontend-state-foundation.summary.md). Unrelated prompt-22/yolopilot files were left untouched."}}
